The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Calcutta, May 3: Keeping the surging inflation in mind, Coal India will not hike prices of thermal coal to check any indirect impact of the mineral on other products, minister of state for coal Santosh Bagrodia said. The minister said the mineral would be abundantly available in the market. He added that 15 million tonnes of coal would be sold through e-auction in May and June.                            
	 New Delhi, May 3: Hero Honda Motor has been hit by a workers strike, forcing the closure of its manufacturing unit at Dharuhera in Haryana.                            
	 Mumbai, May 3: Tata Industries, which was served a Rs 45-crore tax demand notice by the income tax department for buying a Rs 660-crore stake from AT amp;T, has paid the amount.
                                                                                                                         
